---
import MarketingLayout from "../layouts/MarketingLayout.astro";

const lastUpdated = "December 31, 2025";
---

<MarketingLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy Policy for FloImg and FloImg Studio - how we collect, use, and protect your data"
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 mb-12">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <div class="prose prose-zinc dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <!-- Introduction -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 mb-4">
          Welcome to FloImg! This Privacy Policy explains how Flojo, Inc. ("FloImg", "we", "our", or
          "us") collects, uses, and shares information about you when you use our website and
          services. We value your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information.
        </p>
        <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 mb-4">
          By using our website, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Information We Collect -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
          1. Information We Collect
        </h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 mb-4">
          We collect different types of information depending on how you interact with our website
          and services.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-3">
          a. Information You Provide to Us
        </h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 space-y-2 mb-6">
          <li>
            <strong>Account Information:</strong> When you create an account, we collect your name, email
            address, and authentication details (including OAuth provider information if you sign in with
            Google or GitHub).
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Usage Preferences:</strong> Your workflow configurations, saved templates, and editor
            preferences.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Communication:</strong> If you contact us or provide feedback, we collect your contact
            details and the content of your messages.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-3">
          b. Information Collected Automatically
        </h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 space-y-2 mb-6">
          <li>
            <strong>Usage Data:</strong> Information about your interactions with our website (pages visited,
            features used, workflows executed).
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Device and Log Data:</strong> Your IP address, browser type, operating system, and
            referring URLs.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Analytics:</strong> We use Umami, a privacy-focused analytics service that does not
            use cookies and does not track individual users. See our Cookie Policy below for details.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-3">c. Generated Content</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 mb-4">
          When you use FloImg Studio Cloud, images you generate or upload may be stored temporarily
          for processing. If you save images to the cloud, they are stored in your account until you
          delete them.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- How We Use Your Information -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
          2. How We Use Your Information
        </h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 mb-4">We use the information we collect to:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 space-y-2">
          <li>Provide and improve our services</li>
          <li>Process your image workflows and store generated content</li>
          <li>Manage your account and subscription</li>
          <li>Analyze aggregate usage patterns to improve our offerings</li>
          <li>Respond to your inquiries and provide customer support</li>
          <li>Comply with legal obligations and prevent fraud or abuse</li>
          <li>Enforce our content moderation policies</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Sharing Your Information -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
          3. Sharing Your Information
        </h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 mb-4">
          We do not sell your personal information. We may share your data in the following
          circumstances:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 space-y-2">
          <li>
            <strong>AI Service Providers:</strong> When you use AI features, your prompts and images are
            sent to third-party AI providers (OpenAI, Stability AI, Google, etc.) according to their respective
            privacy policies.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Infrastructure Providers:</strong> We use cloud hosting and storage providers (Hetzner,
            Cloudflare) to deliver our services.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Payment Processors:</strong> Stripe processes payments and has access to billing information.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Legal Compliance:</strong> We may share information if required by law or in response
            to legal requests.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Business Transfers:</strong> In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets,
            your information may be transferred to the new entity.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Your Privacy Rights -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
          4. Your Privacy Rights
        </h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 mb-4">
          Depending on your location, you may have certain rights regarding your personal
          information:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 space-y-2 mb-4">
          <li>
            <strong>Access:</strong> You can request a copy of your personal data.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Correction:</strong> You can ask us to update or correct inaccurate information.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Deletion:</strong> You can request that we delete your account and personal data,
            subject to legal limitations.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Opt-out:</strong> You can opt out of analytics tracking via our cookie settings.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Data Portability:</strong> You can request an export of your data in a portable format.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300">
          To exercise your rights, contact us at <a
            href="mailto:privacy@goflojo.com"
            class="text-teal-600 dark:text-teal-400 hover:underline">privacy@goflojo.com</a
          >.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Data Security -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-4">5. Data Security</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 mb-4">
          We use industry-standard measures to protect your personal information, including:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 space-y-2">
          <li>HTTPS encryption for all data in transit</li>
          <li>Secure, httpOnly cookies for authentication</li>
          <li>Regular security audits and updates</li>
          <li>Access controls and authentication for internal systems</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 mt-4">
          However, no system is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Data Retention -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-4">6. Data Retention</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 mb-4">
          We retain your information as long as necessary to provide our services:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 space-y-2">
          <li>
            <strong>Account data:</strong> Retained while your account is active, deleted upon account
            deletion request.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Generated images:</strong> Retained until you delete them, or upon account deletion.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Analytics data:</strong> Aggregated, non-personal analytics are retained indefinitely.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Legal holds:</strong> Some data may be retained longer if required by law.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Children's Privacy -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
          7. Children's Privacy
        </h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300">
          FloImg is not intended for individuals under 16. We do not knowingly collect data from
          children. If we discover such data has been collected, it will be deleted promptly.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- International Data Transfers -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
          8. International Data Transfers
        </h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300">
          Your information may be processed in the United States or other jurisdictions where our
          service providers operate. These jurisdictions may have different data protection laws
          than your home country. By using FloImg, you consent to these transfers.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Self-Hosted Version -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
          9. Self-Hosted FloImg Studio
        </h2>
        <div
          class="bg-zinc-100 dark:bg-zinc-800 border border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700 rounded-lg p-6"
        >
          <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 mb-4">
            FloImg Studio is available as open-source software under the MIT License. If you
            self-host FloImg Studio:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 space-y-2">
            <li>This Privacy Policy does not apply to your self-hosted instance</li>
            <li>
              You are responsible for your own data collection, storage, and privacy compliance
            </li>
            <li>No data from self-hosted instances is sent to FloImg servers</li>
            <li>We have no access to or visibility into self-hosted deployments</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Cookies and Tracking -->
      <section class="mb-12" id="cookies">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
          10. Cookies and Tracking Technologies
        </h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 mb-6">
          We use cookies and similar technologies to provide and improve our services. This section
          explains what cookies we use and why.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-3">What Are Cookies?</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 mb-6">
          Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit our website. They help
          us remember your preferences and understand how you use our site.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-3">
          Essential Cookies (Always Active)
        </h3>
        <div
          class="bg-zinc-100 dark:bg-zinc-800 border border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6"
        >
          <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 mb-3">
            These cookies are necessary for our website to function properly and cannot be disabled:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 space-y-1">
            <li>
              <strong>Session Cookie</strong> (<code class="text-sm">floimg_session</code>): Manages
              your login session. Expires after 30 days.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Consent Cookie</strong> (<code class="text-sm">floimg_consent</code>):
              Remembers your cookie preferences. Expires after 1 year.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Analytics (Optional)</h3>
        <div
          class="bg-teal-50 dark:bg-teal-900/20 border border-teal-200 dark:border-teal-800 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6"
        >
          <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 mb-3">
            We use <strong>Umami</strong>, a privacy-focused analytics service:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 space-y-1">
            <li>Does not use cookies</li>
            <li>Does not track individual users</li>
            <li>Does not collect personally identifiable information</li>
            <li>Data is aggregated and anonymized</li>
            <li>Self-hosted on our own infrastructure</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 mt-3">
            You can opt out of analytics tracking via our <a
              href="/cookie-settings"
              class="text-teal-600 dark:text-teal-400 hover:underline">cookie settings</a
            >.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-3">
          Marketing (Not Currently Used)
        </h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 mb-6">
          We do not currently use marketing cookies or advertising trackers. If we add these in the
          future, we will update this policy and request your consent.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Local Storage</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 mb-4">
          In addition to cookies, we use browser local storage for:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 space-y-1">
          <li>
            <strong>Terms Consent</strong>: Remembers if you've accepted the Terms of Service
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>UI Preferences</strong>: Stores your editor preferences and theme settings
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Changes to Privacy Policy -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
          11. Changes to This Privacy Policy
        </h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300">
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If significant changes occur, we will
          notify you via website notice or email. Your continued use of the Service after changes
          are posted constitutes acceptance of the modified Privacy Policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Contact -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-4">12. Contact Us</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300 mb-4">
          If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices,
          please contact us at:
        </p>
        <p class="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-300">
          <strong>Email:</strong>
          <a
            href="mailto:privacy@goflojo.com"
            class="text-teal-600 dark:text-teal-400 hover:underline">privacy@goflojo.com</a
          ><br />
          <strong>Website:</strong>
          <a href="https://floimg.com" class="text-teal-600 dark:text-teal-400 hover:underline"
            >https://floimg.com</a
          >
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Compliance -->
      <section class="mb-8">
        <p class="text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 text-sm">
          This Privacy Policy was created to comply with applicable privacy laws and regulations,
          including the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and the California Consumer
          Privacy Act (CCPA).
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</MarketingLayout>
